stories.text:
I was reading this article on the patents that META want to use in the Metaverse https://12ft.io/proxy?q=http://www.ft.com/content/76d40aac-034e-4e0b-95eb-c5d34146f647

And honestly besides the awful ultra-targeted advertising based on biological reactions etc... it seems actually pretty freaking cool.

Do you think we'll be able to create adblockers for these devices in the future?

For now Occulus is based on android and is pretty hackable, but IYO how will that change if Meta make their own OS?
